<h2 class="bold font-l">Borderlands 2</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
Five years after the original Vault was opened, the Hyperion Corporation has taken over Pandora and begun extensive mining operations for &quot;Eridium&quot;, a precious mineral that has begun to appear across the planet. Led by its president, Handsome Jack (who stole the credit for opening the Vault and defeating the Destroyer), Hyperion's robotic armies have crushed all resistance to Jack's goal of &quot;bringing order&quot; to the savage wastelands. </p>
<p class='example_row'>Example of:<br><a href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroShooter" class='trope-example-link'>Hero Shooter</a></p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="8mm3j0" data-video-descrip="&amp;quot;Short Change Hero&amp;quot; by The Heavy is used in the intro." data-video-title="&quot;Short Change Hero&quot;" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/8mm3j0_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/8mm3j0.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/RealSongThemeTune" data-video-tropename="Real Song Theme Tune" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="VideoGame/Borderlands2" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/8mm3j0.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">"Short Change H...</span></p>
</a>
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="yezl22" data-video-descrip="Krieg, the Psycho, was a Vault Hunter who suffered horrifying experimentation at the hands of the Hyperion Corporation. And while the process made him much stronger, it also drove him to complete insanity not unlike many other psychos in Pandora, with only a fragment of his former, saner self now acting as a conscience to him. With that said, Krieg's inner self is well aware of everything he does, and is nearly unable to do anything about it." data-video-title="Krieg" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/yezl22_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/yezl22.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/ReluctantPsycho" data-video-tropename="Reluctant Psycho" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="VideoGame/Borderlands,VideoGame/Borderlands2" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/yezl22.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Krieg</span></p>
</a>
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="wb2lks" data-video-descrip="Soon after the Vault Hunter kills the Warrior and saves Pandora from annihilation, the once smug and charismatic Handsome Jack suffers a major breakdown upon seeing himself dying and his Evil Plan being ultimately foiled." data-video-title="Handsome Jack's Defeat" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/wb2lks_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/wb2lks.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/VillainousBreakdown" data-video-tropename="Villainous Breakdown" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="VideoGame/Borderlands2,VideoGame/Borderlands" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/wb2lks.jpg">
